    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 14,
        "summary": "Go from the presence of a foolish man\u2014A true witness delivers souls\u2014Righteousness exalts a nation.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Every wise woman buildeth her house: but the foolish plucketh it down with her hands.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Woman.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that walketh in his uprightness feareth the Lord: but he that is perverse in his ways despiseth him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking with God.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "In the mouth of the foolish is a rod of pride: but the lips of the wise shall preserve them.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 30
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Where no oxen are, the crib is clean: but much increase is by the strength of the ox.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A faithful witness will not lie: but a false witness will utter lies.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A scorner seeketh wisdom, and findeth it not: but knowledge is easy unto him that understandeth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 8:9; 15:14; 17:24; 2\u00a0Ne. 9:28.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Go from the presence of a foolish man, when thou perceivest not in him the lips of knowledge.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The wisdom of the prudent is to understand his way: but the folly of fools is deceit.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 28:30.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Deceit.",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Fools make a mock at sin: but among the righteous there is favour.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ether 12:26.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The heart knoweth his own bitterness; and a stranger doth not intermeddle with his joy.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The house of the wicked shall be overthrown: but the tabernacle of the upright shall flourish.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 7:27 (24\u201327).",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0tent.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 63
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "There is a way which seemeth right unto a man, but the end thereof are the ways of death.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 55:8 (8\u20139).",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 15:10.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Even in laughter the heart is sorrowful; and the end of that mirth is heaviness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Laughter.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 2:1.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The backslider in heart shall be filled with his own ways: and a good man shall be satisfied from himself.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The simple believeth every word: but the prudent man looketh well to his going.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prudence.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A wise man feareth, and departeth from evil: but the fool rageth, and is confident.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 4:34; Morm. 3:9; 4:8.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 10
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that is soon angry dealeth foolishly: and a man of wicked devices is hated.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Anger.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 10
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The simple inherit folly: but the prudent are crowned with knowledge.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prudence.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Knowledge.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The evil bow before the good; and the wicked at the gates of the righteous.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The poor is hated even of his own neighbour: but the rich hath many friends.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 56:16.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 19:4.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that despiseth his neighbour sinneth: but he that hath mercy on the poor, happy is he.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 52:40; 104:18.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Happiness.",
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Do they not err that devise evil? but mercy and truth shall be to them that devise good.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "In all labour there is profit: but the talk of the lips tendeth only to penury.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Labor; Work, Value of.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Communication.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 63
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The crown of the wise is their riches: but the foolishness of fools is folly.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Foolishness.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A true witness delivereth souls: but a deceitful witness speaketh lies.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "In the fear of the Lord is strong confidence: and his children shall have a place of refuge.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reverence.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 11
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The fear of the Lord is a fountain of life, to depart from the snares of death.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "In the multitude of people is the king's honour: but in the want of people is the destruction of the prince.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that is slow to wrath is of great understanding: but he that is hasty of spirit exalteth folly.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Self-Mastery.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 15:18; D&C 60:14. TG\u00a0Patience.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Understanding.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 50
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0quick-tempered. TG\u00a0Haste; Rashness.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A sound heart is the life of the flesh: but envy the rottenness of the bones.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Envy.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 826
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that oppresseth the poor reproacheth his Maker: but he that honoureth him hath mercy on the poor.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 24:14 (14\u201315); Prov. 17:5; Matt. 25:45; D&C 56:16. TG\u00a0Oppression.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The wicked is driven away in his wickedness: but the righteous hath hope in his death.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Death of.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wisdom resteth in the heart of him that hath understanding: but that which is in the midst of fools is made known.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Righteousness exalteth a nation: but sin is a reproach to any people.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "4\u00a0Ne. 1:16 (15\u201317). TG\u00a0Righteousness.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The king's favour is toward a wise servant: but his wrath is against him that causeth shame.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}